snippet.textDisplay: @electricmastro Yes, that is what I am talking about.  It was typical of Nintendo to add credits unscrupously for marketing or internal reasons.  I helped found Paradigm, the company that made PilotWings 64, and I had worked with them for 7 years before doing that game.  I wrote, arranged, sequenced, programmed, mixed and installed every track in the game.  Mr. Nakatsuka had nothing to do with the music in the game whatsoever.  Mr. Wada approved each of the tracks on site in Dallas.
snippet.textOriginal: @electricmastro Yes, that is what I am talking about.  It was typical of Nintendo to add credits unscrupously for marketing or internal reasons.  I helped found Paradigm, the company that made PilotWings 64, and I had worked with them for 7 years before doing that game.  I wrote, arranged, sequenced, programmed, mixed and installed every track in the game.  Mr. Nakatsuka had nothing to do with the music in the game whatsoever.  Mr. Wada approved each of the tracks on site in Dallas.
